# 👗 Fashion Wrapped: A Personal Style Analysis

> A Spotify Wrapped-style data story built from my own wardrobe data. 67 pieces, 33 brands, tracked by cost-per-wear, colour palette, and spend patterns across 2025.

**[🔗 View Live Project](https://effulgent-marshmallow-13421e.netlify.app/) 

---

## Overview

Fashion Wrapped is an end-to-end personal data project that treats my wardrobe like a dataset. I collected purchase records and wear-tracking logs, cleaned and analysed the data in Python, and showcased the findings in an interactive scrolling experience. The intention is for it to be styled like a high-fashion editorial.

The project demonstrates the full analyst workflow: raw data → cleaning → analysis → insight generation → data storytelling.

---

## Key Findings

| Metric | Value |
|---|---|
| Total spend | $3,785 |
| Total pieces tracked | 67 |
| Total wears logged | 1,442 |
| Cost per wear | $2.62 |
| Wardrobe retention rate | 99% |
| Unique brands | 33 |
| Peak spend month | September ($847 — 2.7× avg) |
| Best value piece | Anna Field Scarf ($0.30/wear) |

**Top insight:** Aritzia accounts for 17% of total spend across just 4 pieces — the highest avg spend per item at $164 — yet all 4 pieces remain in active rotation with 116 wears logged between them.

---

## Project Structure

```
fashion-wrapped/
│
├── data/
│   └── wardrobe_data.csv          # Personal purchase & wear tracking data
│
├── fashion_wrapped_analysis.ipynb  # Full Python analysis notebook
│
├── fashion_wrapped.html            # Interactive scrolling visual (the "Wrapped")
│
└── README.md
```

---

## Analysis Breakdown

The Jupyter notebook covers 10 sections:

1. **Setup & imports** — Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn, custom colour palette
2. **Data cleaning** — type casting, nulls, derived metrics
3. **Hero KPIs** — total spend, cost-per-wear, retention rate
4. **Colour palette** — breakdown by colour family, % of wardrobe
5. **Category analysis** — spend vs cost-per-wear by category
6. **Brand analysis** — top 10 brands, Pareto concentration
7. **Monthly rhythm** — spend over time with avg benchmark
8. **Cost-per-wear deep dive** — scatter plot + best/worst value pieces
9. **Sustainability score** — retention, secondhand %, wears vs industry benchmark
10. **Style archetype scoring** — data-derived persona traits

---

